       The journey that's Ours
       Gary Hirson
       10
       résumé :
       An adventure-story about self-discovery, The Journey that's Ours
       introduces young readers to their unique individuality and promotes
       growth in self-confidence. In such a fast changing environment with
       exposure to so much more, tools such as mind-mapping, conflict
       resolution, and how the law of attraction really works, are needed
       to help us keep up while staying true to ourselves. Continuing with
       their adventures, teenage siblings Joel and Jina once again meet
       Magic who guides them through the fun and testing elements of their
       everyday lives. Jina falls in love and gets hurt, while Joel has to
       deal with the pains of standing up both on his surfboard and as a
       young man.
